==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intestinal
<hw>In*tes"ti*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intestinal</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the intestines of
an animal; <as>as, the <ex>intestinal</ex> tube; <ex>intestinal</ex>
digestion; <ex>intestinal</ex> enzymes.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Intestinal canal</b></col>. <cd>Same as
<er>Intestine</er>, <pos>n.</pos></cd> -- <col><b>Intestinal
worm</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any species of helminth living in
the intestinal canal of any animal. The species are
numerous.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intestine</ent>⟦br⟧
